"AWSTemplateFormatVersion: \"2010-09-09\"\nDescription: Luciel Step 28 Phase 2 Commit 6 - Application Auto Scaling for luciel-worker-service. CPU TargetTracking at 60 percent, capacity 1-4. Backlog policy deferred (broker not yet verified).\n\nParameters:\n  WorkerClusterName:\n    Type: String\n    Default: luciel-cluster\n    Description: ECS cluster hosting luciel-worker-service.\n  WorkerServiceName:\n    Type: String\n    Default: luciel-worker-service\n    Description: ECS service running the celery worker.\n  MinCapacity:\n    Type: Number\n    Default: 1\n    MinValue: 1\n    Description: Minimum desired count (always-on floor).\n  MaxCapacity:\n    Type: Number\n    Default: 4\n    MinValue: 1\n    Description: Maximum desired count (RDS-bounded ceiling).\n  CpuTargetPercent:\n    Type: Number\n    Default: 60\n    MinValue: 10\n    MaxValue: 90\n    Description: Target average CPU utilization percent for the worker service.\n  ScaleOutCooldownSeconds:\n    Type: Number\n    Default: 60\n    MinValue: 0\n    Description: Seconds to wait after scale-out before another scale-out.\n  ScaleInCooldownSeconds:\n    Type: Number\n    Default: 300\n    MinValue: 0\n    Description: Seconds to wait after scale-in before another scale-in.\n\nResources:\n\n  WorkerScalableTarget:\n    Type: AWS::ApplicationAutoScaling::ScalableTarget\n    Properties:\n      ServiceNamespace: ecs\n      ScalableDimension: ecs:service:DesiredCount\n      ResourceId: !Sub \"service/${WorkerClusterName}/${WorkerServiceName}\"\n      MinCapacity: !Ref MinCapacity\n      MaxCapacity: !Ref MaxCapacity\n      RoleARN: !Sub \"arn:aws:iam::${AWS::AccountId}:role/aws-service-role/ecs.application-autoscaling.amazonaws.com/AWSServiceRoleForApplicationAutoScaling_ECSService\"\n\n  WorkerCpuTargetTrackingPolicy:\n    Type: AWS::ApplicationAutoScaling::ScalingPolicy\n    Properties:\n      PolicyName: luciel-worker-cpu-target-tracking\n      PolicyType: TargetTrackingScaling\n      ScalingTargetId: !Ref WorkerScalableTarget\n      TargetTrackingScalingPolicyConfiguration:\n        TargetValue: !Ref CpuTargetPercent\n        ScaleOutCooldown: !Ref ScaleOutCooldownSeconds\n        ScaleInCooldown: !Ref ScaleInCooldownSeconds\n        DisableScaleIn: false\n        PredefinedMetricSpecification:\n          PredefinedMetricType: ECSServiceAverageCPUUtilization\n\nOutputs:\n  ScalableTargetResourceId:\n    Description: Application Auto Scaling resource ID for the worker service.\n    Value: !Sub \"service/${WorkerClusterName}/${WorkerServiceName}\"\n  CpuPolicyArn:\n    Description: ARN of the CPU TargetTracking scaling policy.\n    Value: !Ref WorkerCpuTargetTrackingPolicy\n  MinCapacityApplied:\n    Description: Effective minimum desired count.\n    Value: !Ref MinCapacity\n  MaxCapacityApplied:\n    Description: Effective maximum desired count.\n    Value: !Ref MaxCapacity\n  CpuTargetApplied:\n    Description: Effective CPU utilization target (percent).\n    Value: !Ref CpuTargetPercent\n"
